# Mosaico development live lab lessons

## Register the workspace before the first launch

The mounted repository being a Git checkout does not populate the isolated
profile's workspace registry. Run once per fresh profile:

```bash
bash containers/mosaico/run --profile claude mosaico channel init
```

This writes only profile-local Mosaico state and creates/resolves the workspace
root channel used by launch.

## Launch configuration is transport-owned

`mosaico agents <target> [prompt]` does not accept provider argv, a harness
override, a command override, or a transport selector. The selected
agent's `harness` points to one `harnesses.json` bundle; that bundle owns
`harness`, `transport`, and `args`. The transport selects PTY, ACP, or app-server.

Put operational provider flags in bundle `args`. Put a supported native profile
name in the agent's optional `profile` string. Use direct mode when testing raw
provider arguments.

## Per-session agents are keyless on disk

With `perSessionKey: true`, omit `secret_key` and `public_key`. Mosaico derives a
fresh session identity from the backend `mosaicoPrivateKey` plus a fresh anchor.
Persist key fields only for an explicit `perSessionKey: false` durable agent.

The device's `userNsec` is the human identity and `mosaicoPrivateKey` is the
backend identity. They must be distinct even in a disposable lab.

## Never inspect a live profile from a second container

A second container for the same bind-mounted profile can replace `daemon.sock`,
run startup cleanup against the live session, and leave the active agent with a
down status or hook timeouts. This applies to all daemon-backed commands,
including:

```text
mosaico
mosaico channel ...
mosaico debug explain ...
mosaico debug hook-tail
```

While a launched container is alive, read bind-mounted logs from the host and
use croissant/`nak`/`probe-lab`. Use the PTY terminal already attached by the
launch helper. Stop the container before same-profile CLI inspection.

## Mentions require tags

Use:

```bash
mosaico channel send --channel <channel> --tag <session-handle> \
  --message "Run mosaico my session."
```

Literal `@handle` text is not a recipient tag. `--force` publishes mention-like
text literally; it does not turn the text into a tagged delivery.

## Reset both Mosaico state stores

Disposable profile resets must remove SQLite `state.db*` and NMP's `nmp.redb`.
Keeping either while switching to a fresh relay can retain stale workspace,
membership, or event state. The profile writer performs this reset by default.

## Use supported operations to prewarm

Exact-profile `doctor` builds Mosaico and installs the relevant provider
integration. ACP/app-server `smoke` then proves the configured transport and
real model auth. Do not use an unsupported top-level version flag as a build
shortcut.

## Cleanup uses recorded container ids

`scripts/cleanup-lab` reads cidfiles under the lab work directory, stops those
containers, and then stops the relay PID from `lab.env`. Always clean containers
before the relay so live agents do not reconnect or mutate the next run.
